In this article, President Trump holds a signing ceremony in the Oval Office for the tax cut bill that was recently passed. He discusses the benefits of the bill, including tax cuts for American families, incentives for businesses, and the repeal of the individual mandate in Obamacare. He also mentions other accomplishments of his administration, such as the defeat of ISIS and progress in Afghanistan. The President expresses his gratitude to the members of Congress who worked on the bill and predicts that it will be popular with the American people. He concludes by saying that he believes there will be bipartisan work done in the future, particularly on infrastructure.